# act configuration — see CLAUDE.md "Validating workflows locally with `act`"
#
# Pin `ubuntu-latest` to catthehacker's medium image (Ubuntu 24.04-based, matches
# GitHub's current `ubuntu-latest` runner). The act default image is intentionally
# minimal and silently breaks Node/pnpm setups.
#
# Architecture is deliberately NOT pinned — act defaults to the host arch. On
# Apple Silicon that's arm64 (fast, native). This repo has no arch-sensitive code
# and tools downloaded inside the workflows (actionlint, yamllint) ship arm64
# builds. To strictly mirror real `ubuntu-latest` (amd64) for parity debugging,
# append `--container-architecture linux/amd64` to the command.
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest
